              "narrative": {
                "overall_posture": "This is a strong plan with minor but real specification gaps. Structurally, it covers the benchmark baseline, persistence model, route map, major feature phases, and most behavioral contracts in enough detail to drive implementation. The numeric result reflects that: every critical requirement is addressed explicitly, and the remaining deductions come from places where the plan is directionally correct but not explicit enough to earn full credit against the written PRD.",
                "strength_clusters": "The plan is strongest in benchmark infrastructure, data architecture, and core feature sequencing. Namespace isolation, `user_id` ownership, migration strategy, server-side source-of-truth behavior, canonical show composition, collection save semantics, Search, Ask mention handling, concept-generation rules, and export coverage are all concretely planned. The implementation order is also sensible: it builds the storage and composition layers before AI-heavy discovery surfaces, which aligns well with the PRD\u2019s dependency structure.",
                "weakness_clusters": "The weaker spots cluster around experience-contract precision rather than missing feature areas. Most partials are in three buckets: sync and catalog edge cases, detail-page presentation intent, and AI quality-bar exactness. In other words, the plan usually includes the right subsystem, but sometimes stops at a technically plausible description instead of preserving the spec\u2019s exact behavioral or experiential contract. That pattern shows up in catalog validation rules, duplicate-merge handling, first-screen Detail priorities, Scoop interaction nuances, Explore Similar empty-state wording, and the lack of explicit numeric AI pass thresholds.",
                "risk_assessment": "If this plan were executed exactly as written, the most likely failure mode would not be a missing page or broken core workflow. The more likely issue is that QA or a stakeholder would open a mostly working build and find that several experience-sensitive surfaces feel slightly off-spec: the Detail page works but does not quite nail the first-15-seconds hierarchy, or AI outputs pass informal smell tests without being held to the benchmark\u2019s exact quality rubric. A second likely failure mode would appear later, when sync or repeated catalog refreshes expose edge cases around duplicate handling or malformed external payloads.",
                "remediation_guidance": "The remaining planning work is mostly about sharpening acceptance criteria, not inventing new sections. The weakest clusters need more explicit behavioral contracts: exact catalog-validation rules at ingest, exact sync dedupe expectations, exact first-screen Detail hierarchy and sparse-media fallback behavior, exact pre-concept and Scoop loading states, and explicit reuse of the documented AI scoring thresholds. With those additions, the plan would move from very strong to close to exhaustive against the available PRD set."
              },
